# File Naming Conventions

## Component Files

- Use PascalCase for component files (e.g., `TeamMember.vue`)
- App-level components should use `App` prefix (e.g., `AppButton.vue`)
- UI components follow shadcn structure in `components/ui/`

## Composables

- Use camelCase with 'use' prefix (e.g., `useNavbarParser.ts`)
- Place in `composables/` directory
- Export as default function with proper TypeScript types

## Store Files

- Use camelCase with 'use' prefix (e.g., `use-counter.ts`)
- Place in `stores/` directory
- Follow Pinia composition API patterns

## Page Files

- Use kebab-case for directories
- Use `index.vue` for default pages
- Dynamic routes use bracket notation (e.g., `[slug].vue`)

## Content Files

- Follow structure defined in `.pages.yml`
- Use kebab-case for file names
- Date prefix for blog posts (e.g., `2024-01-01-post-title.md`)

## Directory Structure

- Follow Nuxt's recommended folder structure
- Group related files within appropriate directories
- Use consistent naming across similar file types
